# Restart command (copy button)

Whenever you tell the user to **restart** the Transform Sim bot for this repo (`claude-slack-bot-mcp`), **always** include **exactly one** Markdown **fenced code block** using `bash` as the language, with **nothing on the same line as the opening fence** and **only the restart command inside** (one line), so the UI shows a **copy** control.

Use this block verbatim (path matches this workspace):

```bash
cd /Users/jackpilon/claude-slack-bot-mcp && npm run startup
```

Do not substitute `npm run start` unless the user explicitly runs without ngrok; default to `npm run startup` per `README-MCP.md` / `scripts/startup.sh`.

If they run the **original** repo instead, use:

```bash
cd /Users/jackpilon/claude-slack-bot && npm run startup
```

Only when they are clearly working in `claude-slack-bot`, not this MCP copy.
